article.headline: Saint Joseph's 75, Boston U. 68
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Langston Galloway scored a career-high 30 points to lead Saint Joseph's to a 75-68 win over Boston University on Wednesday night. Galloway shot 9 for 14 from the field, while making a career-best 6 of 8 3-pointers. His last one came with 2:11 to play after BU had cut the deficit to 66-61. The Hawks (6-3) closed out the game 6 for 11 from the foul line. Junior Carl Jones became the 48th Saint Joseph's player to reach 1,000 points when he hit a jumper with 2 seconds to go in the first half. Jones finished with 13 for 1,007 career points. The Terriers (4-5) were led by Darryl Partin with 24 points. The Hawks used a 10-0 run in the final 3:45 of the first half to lead 40-28 at the break. C.J. Aiken, the nation's leader in blocked shots with a 5.0 average, added five for Saint Joseph's.
